Mr. Gbenga Adefaye, the General Manager/Editor-in-Chief of Vanguard Newspapers, has been appointed as Provost of the Nigerian Institute of Journalism, Ogba, Ikeja. A statement signed in Lagos on Monday by former Ogun governor, Chief Olusegun Osoba, Chairman, Governing Council of the NIJ, said Adefaye would serve as Provost of the institution with effect from Sept. 1, 2020, pending the appointment of a new Provost. He succeeds the former Provost, Mr. Gbemiga Oluleye, who has served out his term meritoriously. Adefaye was a former two-term president of the Nigerian Guild of Editors. The NIJ is a Nigerian monotechnic institute located at Ogba in Ikeja, Lagos State. It is a diploma-awarding monotechnic established in 1963 by the International Press Institute. (NAN) By Ismaila Chafe   Abuja -  President Muhammadu Buhari has urged the Provost of Nigerian Institute of Journalism (NIJ), Mr Gbemiga Ogunleye, to use his versatile experience in setting proper standards for journalists in the country. The president made the call  in a congratulatory message issued by Presidential Spokesman, Femi… January 6, 2019 In "News" LAGOS - Steve Nwosu, forrmer Deputy Managing Director of The Sum; Rose Moses, former editor of Daily Times and publisher of Newsmart online newspaper and Abdulfatah Oladeinde, former editor of The Sun, along with other high ranking editors will on Saturday, December 22, launch Nigeria's newest tabloid, The Nigerian Xpress… December 21, 2018 In "Top Stories" LAGOS - No fewer than 70 sympathisers on Friday signed the condolence register of  the immediate past Managing Director of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN),  Dame Oluremi Oyo, who died on Oct.1. Oyo, a former presidential Spokesperson and a former President of the Guild of Editors, died at a… October 3, 2014 In "News"